      "comment": "JOYHOUSE ROCK (9) was very impressive here on debut despite jumping a $26 chance, missing out on the win in a photo finish. This looks to shape similarly with the slight rise in trip suiting. Can improve sharply on the debut effort and if the gaps come on straightening, she can get the job done this time. DEEPLY ROOTED (4) was able to settle a touch closer last start despite the wide draw last time out, missing 4.1L off the winner. Drawn better again with Cheung claiming a couple of kilos. Can land the knockout blow this time around. MOJO MIO (6) couldn't hold on when leading them up over 1100m last start when off a 73-day break. He did jump favourite there and he'll be better for that effort. Missed as favourite last start but can turn in a better effort this time. ACOUSTIC BUBBLES (10) joins the David Smith barn today and is not to be discounted. MAHLER'S MELODY (8) won a trial coming into this in her first public outing for the Hall barn. Can make an impression.",
